content:
Hi @Saul Kravitz looks like there is an interesting quirk with 0.1.6. Organization.telecom is in the Differential table, but crossed out. And Organization.telecom is in the spreadsheet from the site downloads. However, Organization.telecom is not in the snapshot. Any idea what is going on here? Should I submit a JIRA ticket?

Also, what is alias?
interestingly this is only on the Network profile not the org profile named Plan-Net Organization, but the actual StructureDefinitions look right to me.. maybe it's an IG Publisher bug?

@Jason Teeple -- I'm not seeing what you are referring to.
Then again, don't actually review the IG publisher outputs beyond the html ones (e.g., https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/davinci-pdex-plan-net/StructureDefinition-plannet-Organization.html) where all appears fine.

Oh, That is intentional, and a carryover from the VhDir heritage of Plan-Net (http://hl7.org/fhir/uv/vhdir/2018Sep/StructureDefinition-vhdir-network.html)
The network is required to be 'partOf' an Organization, and the telecom info is expected to be found there.
There remains a contact field with telecom information. @Jason Teeple
